# Login Test Cases

## Overview
This document contains manual test cases for the Login feature of a web application.  
The purpose of these test cases is to ensure the login functionality works correctly under various conditions, including valid, invalid, and edge-case scenarios.

---

## Test Data
- Valid Username: Admin 
- Valid Password: admin123
- Invalid Username: 123admin
- Invalid Password: Admin123422 

---

## Test Cases

| Test Case ID | Test Scenario (Positive/Negative Case) | Preconditions | Test Steps | Expected Result |
|-------------|---------------|------------|----------------|----------|--------|
| TC-LOGIN-01 | Success Login (Positive Case) | Success access login page | 1. Enter valid username<br>2. Enter valid password<br>3. Click Login | User is successfully logged in and redirected to dashboard |
| TC-LOGIN-02 | Failed Login - input invalid username (Negative Case) | Success access login page | 1. Enter invalid username<br>2. Enter valid password<br>3. Click Login | User is failed login and it show "Invalid credentials" message |
| TC-LOGIN-03 | Failed Login - input invalid password (Negative Case) | Success access login page | 1. Enter valid username<br>2. Enter invalid password<br>3. Click Login | User is failed login and it show "Invalid credentials" message |
